TypeSpec uses `@discriminator` decorator to add a discriminator to a model.

<ClientTabs>
<ClientTabItem lang="typespec" >

TypeSpec now has two ways to represent a discriminated set.

1. Use model

```typespec
@discriminator("kind")
model Cat {
  kind: string;
}

model Siamese extends Cat {
  kind: "siamese";
}

model Ragdoll extends Cat {
  kind: "ragdoll";
}
```

The type of the discriminator property could be an enum (extensible or fixed):

```typespec
@discriminator("kind")
model Cat {
  kind: CatKind;
}

union CatKind {
  string,
  Siamese: "siamese",
  Ragdoll: "ragdoll",
}

model Siamese extends Cat {
  kind: CatKind.Siamese;
}

model Ragdoll extends Cat {
  kind: CatKind.Ragdoll;
}
```

2. Use union

```typespec
@discriminator("kind")
union Cat {
  Siamese,
  Ragdoll,
}

model Siamese {}

model Ragdoll {}
```

</ClientTabItem>
